    <detaileddescription>
<para>This header contains is an adapted version of std::stop_token for futures rather than threads.</para>
<para>The main difference in this implementation is 1) the reference counter does not distinguish between/// tokens and sources, and 2) there is no stop_callback.</para>
<para>The API was initially adapted from Baker Josuttis&apos; reference implementation for C++20: <simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://github.com/josuttis/jthread">https://github.com/josuttis/jthread</ulink></para>
</simplesect>
Although the jfuture class is obviously different from std::jthread, this stop_token is not different from std::stop_token. The main goal here is just to provide a stop source in C++17. In the future, we might replace this with an alias to a C++20 std::stop_token. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
